      • storeData

        public abstract void storeData(java.lang.Object invokedObject,
                               java.lang.String className,
                               java.lang.String methodName,
                               java.lang.Object[] paramValues,
                               java.lang.Throwable thrownException,
                               java.lang.Object returnValue,
                               ISDKDataContext sdkContext)
                        throws ReflectorException
        This method places data into the provided ISDKDataContext via the ISDKDataContext.storeData(String, Object) method. Everything in the context will be added to the current snapshot. The context will be cleared after every invocation.
        Parameters:
        invokedObject - The invoked object
        className - The name of the class this method was called on.
        methodName - The name of the method invoked.
        paramValues - The parameters of the invoked method
        thrownException - The exception thrown by this invocation of the method.
        returnValue - The return value of the method
        sdkContext - The place to stash data to place in the snapshot
        Throws:
        ReflectorException
